
<ul> 
  <li>
    Step one: <u> Registration and login </u> <br> 
    At first you have to register at coma and login. <br>
    Notice: You only need one account for all conferences you want to take part in.<br>
    <br>
  </li>
  <li>
     Step two: <u> Create a new conference </u> <br>
     After loging in you find a menu-item '<a href="./help.php?for=conference_create{&popup}{&SID}">
     create conference</a>' where you can specify general conference data. <br>
     Under the item ''<a href="./help.php?for=conference_create{&popup}{&SID}"> advanced settings </a>'
     you have the possibility to adjust further setting. <br>
     If you create a new conference, you are automatically  'chair' of this conference. <br>
     <br>
  </li>
  <li>
    Step three: <u>  Administrate the conference </u> <br>
    After loging in you can 
    <a href="./help.php?for=chair_users{&popup}{&SID}">manage users</a>, 
    <a href="./help.php?for=chair_papers{&popup}{&SID}">papers</a>,
    <a href="./help.php?for=chair_reviews{&popup}{&SID}">reviews</a> and 
    <a href="./help.php?for=chair_confconfig{&popup}{&SID}">change the settings</a>
    of the conference.  <br> 
  </li>
